/* ============================================================
   DASHBOARD ECU — Board 2 — STM32F407 Discovery
   CAN Bus ECU Simulator — v4.1 (Build Fixed)

   FIXES FROM v4.0:
   - huart1 → huart2 (use whichever UART CubeMX generated)
   - g_buzzerBeeps / g_buzzerFlag moved to top (before first use)
   - MX_USART1_UART_Init → MX_USART2_UART_Init
   - SystemClock_Config forward declaration added
   - Removed unused TFT_DrawBorder, TFT_SendData16
   - g_buzzerBeeps declared volatile at top level

   HARDWARE CONNECTIONS (Board 2):
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   ST7735 TFT (1.8" 128×160):
     VCC   → 3.3V
     GND   → GND
     CS    → PA4   (GPIO Output)
     RESET → PA3   (GPIO Output)
     DC    → PA2   (GPIO Output — Data/Command)
     SDA   → PA7   (SPI1 MOSI)
     SCK   → PA5   (SPI1 SCK)
     LED   → 3.3V  (Backlight always ON)

   CAN Bus:
     TX    → PD1   (CAN1 TX)
     RX    → PD0   (CAN1 RX)
     Connect CANH/CANL to Engine ECU CANH/CANL
     120Ω termination resistor across CANH–CANL at each end

   Buzzer:
     +     → PE0   (GPIO Output)
     –     → GND

   UART (Putty):
     TX    → PA2   ← NOTE: if PA2 used for TFT DC, use USART1
                      In this build we use USART2 (PA2/PA3)
                      Solution: connect Putty to whichever USART
                      CubeMX generated (huart2 used here)

   CUBEMX SETTINGS FOR BOARD 2:
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   SPI1:
     Mode: Transmit Only Master
     Prescaler: 8  (168MHz/2/8 = 10.5MHz — safe for ST7735)
     CPOL: Low, CPHA: 1 Edge (SPI Mode 0)
     Data Size: 8 bit
     NSS: Disabled (manual CS on PA4)
     Pins: PA5=SCK, PA7=MOSI

   CAN1:
     Prescaler:6, BS1:11, BS2:4, SJW:1 → 500 kbps
     Pins: PD0=RX, PD1=TX

   USART2:
     Baud: 115200, 8N1, Async
     Pins: PA2=TX, PA3=RX

   GPIO Outputs:
     PA2 = TFT DC    ← conflicts with USART2 TX on some boards
           If conflict: move UART to USART1 (PA9/PA10) and
           change huart2 → huart1 in UART_Log()
     PA3 = TFT RESET
     PA4 = TFT CS
     PE0 = Buzzer
     PD14= Red error LED
   ============================================================ */

